CSS Padding:

The CSS padding properties are used to create space around element's content, inside of any defined borders.

padding Properties:
# padding-top
# padding-right
# padding-bottom
# padding-left

All these properties are used to set the padding of the element.
All these properties can have following values:

## Fixed Values
## Percentage
## inherit



==>inherit:

With this value, the element inherits its padding properties from its parent element.

Shorthand:
padding: TRBL

Width of the element:

To maintain the width of the element, use the box-sizing property & its border-box value, since the value of the element increase with the increase in padding.
